350
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:18,800
Thank you. Thank you. And for
my next piece of evidence--

351
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:20,640
Uh, I think we'd better
leave it there.

352
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:22,800
-All right.
-COUNSEL: Excellent evidence.

353
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:24,120
Thank you very much.

354
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:30,120
Now, Mr. Njorl, will you tell
the court, please,

355
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:34,840
uh, where were you
on the night of 11/26?

356
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:41,040
Move any part of your body
if you were north of a line

357
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:42,960
from the Humber to the Mersey.

358
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,120
Is he in there,
do you think?

359
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:49,880
Hello? Hello?
Defendant, are you there?

360
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:52,800
Coo-ee! Defendant?

361
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:55,200
Uh, I think you'd better go
and have a look, Maurice.

362
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:58,440
-Don't call me Maurice in court.
-I'm sorry.

363
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:04,520
Are you in there?
Mr. Njorl?

364
00:18:08,120 --> 00:18:11,920
This way, Davis.
He's not getting away
this time.

365
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:13,800
We'll try and trap him
in the left lung.

366
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:15,640
If we surround the left lung

367
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:17,360
then we can get in the kidney
and get in the left, okay?

